org.life.sl.utils
Class Timer

java.lang.Object
  org.life.sl.utils.Timer

public class Timer
extends java.lang.Object

Utility class for timing purposes. Use Timer(double int0, double int1) or init() to start the timer, getRunTime(boolean) to return the consumed time, and showProgress(double) to show a progress indicator. The progress indicator works at 2 levels specified by progressInterval

Author:
Bernhard Barkow
